## Backend Setup

The backend relies on three core configuration files (Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml, and
.dockerignore) to orchestrate the environment. Database performance optimizations and initial
seed data are managed atomically within the Django migration lifecycle.

  1. Navigate to the backend directory:

       cd backend

  2. Build and launch the container infrastructure:

     This command pulls the required images, configures isolated networks, attaches volumes for
     data persistence, and starts the services:

       docker-compose up --build

  3. Apply database migrations and populate seed data:

       docker-compose exec web python manage.py migrate

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Frontend Setup

The client application runs natively on your host machine to avoid container filesystem
synchronization overhead, optimizing the frontend developer experience.

  1. Navigate to the frontend directory:

       cd tms-frontend

  2. Install project dependencies:

       npm install

  3. Launch the local development server:

       npm run dev

Frontend Endpoint: http://localhost:5173
##Frontend Endpoint: http://localhost:5173

