## Using the TMS Dashboard

User Scope
  As a user, you can view only the tasks assigned to you and mark them as completed. Assigned
  tasks are visible immediately on login. 10 users are pre-populated via seed migration.

Admin Scope

  1. View an Existing Task
     Look up any task by its task_id.

  2. Create a Task
     Select the task creation option and provide a task title along with an assignment eligibility
     criteria. Three fields are currently supported, with the application designed to accommodate
     new criteria with minimal changes. The three supported operators, specified verbatim, are
     EQUALS, GREATER_THAN_OR_EQUAL, and LESS_THAN. Example criteria:

     [
       {"field": "department", "operator": "EQUALS", "value": "Engineering"},
       {"field": "experience_years", "operator": "GREATER_THAN_OR_EQUAL", "value": 3},
       {"field": "active_tasks_count", "operator": "LESS_THAN", "value": 5}
     ]

     Once created, a task_id will be generated and displayed in a dialog. Save this ID as it is
     required for future reassignments.

  3. Reassign an Existing Task
     Provide a task_id and updated eligibility criteria. The interface mirrors task creation.
     Reassignment is not supported for tasks that are already marked completed.
